=============================================================
This README contains description of CS425 MP1. In This MP,
Two ordered multicast protocol: causal and total ordering
are implemented in C++. The implementation has three steps,
one is built upon another. Step1: unicast with artificial 
delay. Step2: multicast. Step3: multicast with causal or
total ordering. For further infomation please contact author
Wei Yang via email: weiyang4 AT illinois DOT edu.

This description has three parts:
1. Files contained
2. Implementation Detail
3. Execute program
=============================================================

================
Files contained:
mp1.cpp
mp1
config
README

=====================
Implementation Detail:

1. step2: Simulating network delays
	

2. step3: Ordered Multicast Protocol

	1) causal ordering

	2) total ordering

================
Execute program:	

## To compile
>> clang++ mp1.cpp -o mp1 -lpthread

## To run

1) to demo causal ordering
>> ./mp1 config 1 causal
>> ./mp1 config 2 causal
>> ./mp1 config 3 causal
>> ./mp1 config 4 causal

2) to demo total ordering
>> ./mp1 config 1 total
>> ./mp1 config 2 total
>> ./mp1 config 3 total
>> ./mp1 config 4 total

3) to send message from process1 to other processes:
>> msend Hello, I am process1

4) to exit program
>> exit